data.title: Masonic Memorial Temple - Brisbane - 1928
data.meta_description:
Ann Street, Brisbane.
	This is an exceptional example of a Classical Revival building with its huge fluted Corinthian columns. It was designed by Lange Powell, himself a mason, and has been the centre of Queensland's masonic activities.
	
	According to Bill MacMahon in his excellent book, 'Architecture of East Australia', this is a "wonderful building which presents to the street a dignified and slightly mysterious air."
data.text:
Ann Street, Brisbane.

This is an exceptional example of a Classical Revival building with its huge fluted Corinthian columns. It was designed by Lange Powell, himself a mason, and has been the centre of Queensland's masonic activities.

According to Bill MacMahon in his excellent book, 'Architecture of East Australia', this is a "wonderful building which presents to the street a dignified and slightly mysterious air."
